4 D. The assistant funeral director shall complete continuing
5 education in accordance with the provision of Section 396.5b of
6 Title 59 of the Oklahoma Statutes.
7 SECTION 2. AMENDATORY 59 O.S. 2021, Section 396, as
8 amended by Section 1, Chapter 32, O.S.L. 2023 (59 O.S. Supp. 2024,
9 Section 396), is amended to read as follows:
10 Section 396. There is hereby re-created, to continue until July
11 1, 2024 2029, in accordance with the provisions of the Oklahoma
12 Sunset Law, the Oklahoma Funeral Board. Any reference in the
13 statutes to the Oklahoma State Board of Embalmers and Funeral
14 Directors shall be a reference to the Oklahoma Funeral Board. The
15 Board shall consist of seven (7) persons, who shall be appointed by
16 the Governor. The term of membership of each member of the Board
17 shall be five (5) years from the expiration of the term of the
18 member succeeded. Any member having served as a member of the Board
19 shall be eligible for reappointment. Provided that, a member of the
20 Board shall serve no more than two consecutive terms and any
21 unexpired term that a member is appointed to shall not apply to this
22 limit. The Governor shall appoint the necessary members to the
23 Board upon vacancies and immediately prior to the expiration of the
24 various terms. Upon request of the Governor, appointments of a
