13 a resident of this state during the entire time the person serves on
14 the Board. Two of the members of the Board shall be chosen from the
15 general public, one of whom shall, if possible, be a person licensed
16 and actively engaged in the health care field, and shall not be
17 licensed funeral directors or embalmers or have any interest,
18 directly or indirectly, in any funeral establishment or any business
19 dealing in funeral services, supplies or equipment. These two
20 members shall be appointed to serve for five-year terms.
